{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> αὐλίζομαι</b>, <br /> <i>aorist 1</i> ηὐλισάμην always in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus, as 4.13, 6.7\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>], compare (κατ-) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Timoleon” 12\">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]; ηὐλίσθην always in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus, as “An.” 4.1.11, +others; both in 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus, as 8.9\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] (ἐν-), [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 9.15: late \">Refs</a>]<i>future</i> αὐλισθήσομαι[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Tob.6.10\">LXX</a>]: <i>perfect</i> ηὔλισμαι[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Arrianus Historicus “Anabasis” 3.29.7, 1st c.AD: Josephus Historicus “Bellum Judaicum” 1.17.5\">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]:—<b>lie in the</b> αὐλή or <b>courtyard,</b> μυκηθμοῦ.. βοῶν αὐλιζομενάων[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 12.265; κλαγγὴ.. συῶν αὐλιζομενάων 14.412\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; <b>take up one's abode, lodge, live</b> in a place, ἐν ἄντρῳ, of sheep, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 9.93\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; περὶ τὴν λίμνην, of birds,[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3.110, compare 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Historia Animalium” 619a30; οἵοις ἐν πέπλοις αὐ. 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Electra” 304; ἄδειπνος.. ηὐλιζόμην \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<b>passed the night,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Eupolis Comicus 322\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; especially as military term, <b>encamp, bivouac,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 8.9\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: in Medicine texts, of blood, <b>lodge</b> or <b>settle</b> in a place, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Aretaeus Medicus “περὶ αἰτιῶν καὶ σημείων ὀξέων παθῶν” 2.2 (nisi to be read ἁλισθέν)\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]: <i>metaphorically</i>, τὸ ἑσπέρας αὐλισθήσεται κλαυθμός[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Psa.29(30).6. \">LXX</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <i>active</i>, <b>cause to dwell,</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"LXX.Jer.38(31).9, 1st-2nd c.AD: Dio Chrysostomus Sophista 35.16.\">LXX+1st c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G0835","accentedUnicode":"αὐλίζομαι","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0833","matchingForm":"αὐλή","stepTransliteration":"aulē","gloss":"palace/courtyard","_zh_tw_Gloss":"院子","_es_Gloss":"palacio/patio","_zh_Gloss":"院子"}],"shortDef":"to spend the night, find lodging","mediumDef":"to spend the night, find lodging <br /><i>primarily</i> <b>to pass the time in a court-yard; to lodge;</b> hence, <b>to pass the night</b> in any place, <b>to lodge at night, pass</b> or <b>remain through the night,</b> <ref='Mat.21.17'>Mt. 21:17</ref>; <ref='Luk.21.37'>Lk. 21:37</ref>*","stepGloss":"to spend the night","stepTransliteration":"aulizomai","count":2,"_es_Definition":"pasar la noche","_zh_tw_Definition":"過夜 (太 21:17; 路 21:37)","_zh_Definition":"过夜 (太 21:17; 路 21:37)","_step_Type":"verb","_vi_Definition":"trú đêm; nghỉ đêm","_zh_tw_Gloss":"住宿","_es_Gloss":"pasar la noche","_zh_Gloss":"住宿"}]}